$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(2,20,2) ;
$pi = 4*arctan(1);

BEGIN_TEXT

If  \(x = $a \cos^3 \theta \) and \(y = $a \sin^3 \theta \), 
find the total length of the curve swept out by the point \( (x,y) \) as \( \theta \) ranges from \( 0 \) to \( 2\pi.\) 
$BR$BR
Answer: \{ans_rule(20)\}

END_TEXT

ANS(num_cmp("$a*6"));

